        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 5:01PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Kilpatrick Lake, or 16 miles west of Alliance, moving southeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alliance, Angora, and Kilpatrick Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
